<dec f='halide/llvm-install/include/llvm/IR/BasicBlock.h' l='387' type='void llvm::BasicBlock::dropAllReferences()'/>
<doc f='halide/llvm-install/include/llvm/IR/BasicBlock.h' l='379'>/// Cause all subinstructions to &quot;let go&quot; of all the references that said
  /// subinstructions are maintaining.
  ///
  /// This allows one to &apos;delete&apos; a whole class at a time, even though there may
  /// be circular references... first all references are dropped, and all use
  /// counts go to zero.  Then everything is delete&apos;d for real.  Note that no
  /// operations are valid on an object that has &quot;dropped all references&quot;,
  /// except operator delete.</doc>
